-# Bug reporting
-
-If you're having trouble with GNOME OS then we
-want to know. So please file a bug whether it is
-hardware related or behavior related.
-
-## Process for bug reporting
-
-### Hardware
-
-GNOME OS hardware support is not fully complete
-and so we would be interested in if you have
-problems with GNOME OS on your hardware.
-
-**Note: GNOME OS does not support 32 bit architecture. **
-
-When reporting bugs in regards to hardware. If
-there are problems with booting please consider:
-
-Booting with the following kernel
-boot parameters:
-* remove quiet and splash
-* add earlycon=efifb video=efifb systemd.debug_shell=1 rd.systemd.debug_shell=1
-
-This will help us figure out what is going wrong.
-Please also make sure to refer to the [hardware
-compatibility list](https://pad.gnome.org/L6jFCDo8TiKpojF3eq8xBw?view#) to see if your hardware is supported and if not what is missing. If your hardware is not on the list, please help update the list and file bugs.
-
-
-### Software
-
-GNOME OS relies on various parts of systemd
-including systemd-repart, systemd-homed,
-systemd-sysext amongst others. Of course, if
-there are issues with GNOME components then
-please file bugs as well. 
-
-For systemd related items, please file a
-[bug](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-build-meta/-/issues/new).
-
-For specific GNOME related bugs, please file a
-bug in our GNOME gitlab located at
-https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME. Find the proper
-component and then file a bug there.
-
-
