-# openqa.gnome.org deployment
-
-The server is deployed into GNOME's OpenShift server from this repo: https://gitlab.gnome.org/Infrastructure/openshift-images/openqa.
-
-If you have a GNOME LDAP account you can request access via the infrastructure team. 
-
-With permissions, you'll be able to access the OpenShift project at: https://console-openshift-console.apps.openshift.gnome.org/k8s/cluster/projects/openqa
-
-If you look into [pods](https://console-openshift-console.apps.openshift.gnome.org/k8s/ns/openqa/pods) you can view logs and get to a real terminal in the machine:
-
-![image](uploads/21416aecec4cf708222031bb0b3a68fb/image.png){width=900 height=526}
-
-![image](uploads/591241075785da06e1d32216840ed603/image.png){width=900 height=526}
-
-## History
-
-This server was initially deployed by hand to a VM. The deployment was then automated using Ansible in https://gitlab.gnome.org/sthursfield/openqa-ansible. All that is gone now!
